14 (1) 'Certified community health worker' means an individual to whom the committee has
15 issued a certificate to serve as a certified community health worker based on standards
16 and requirements established by the committee.
17 (2) 'Committee' means the Georgia Community Health Worker Certification Committee
18 established by Code Section 31-31-2.
19 (3) 'Community health worker' means a frontline health worker who is a trusted member
20 of a community or has a demonstrated knowledge or unusually close understanding of
21 the community and individuals served and:
22 (A) Provides culturally appropriate health education, information, and outreach in
23 community based settings such as homes, schools, clinics, shelters, local businesses,
24 and community centers;
25 (B) Bridges or culturally mediates between individuals, communities, and health and
26 human services, including actively building individual and community capacity;
27 (C) Assures that community members access the services they need;
28 (D) Provides direct services, such as informal counseling, social support, care
29 coordination, and health screenings;
30 (E) Advocates for individual and community needs; and
31 (F) Provides any additional services as may be identified by the committee that may
32 emerge in the development of community health worker practice.
33 (4) 'Core competencies' means the knowledge and skills a certified community health
34 worker is expected to demonstrate in order to carry out the mission and goals of the
35 profession. Such term includes, but is not limited to, communication skills; interpersonal
36 and relationship-building skills; service coordination and navigation skills;
37 capacity-building skills; advocacy skills; education and facilitation skills; individual and
38 community assessment skills; community outreach and engagement skills; professional
39 skills and conduct; evaluation and research skills; and knowledge base.
