40 (5) 'Training program' means an education and training program that meets the
41 curriculum and training required for a community health worker to be eligible for
42 certification and that has been approved by the committee based on standards and
43 requirements established by the committee. Reserved.
44 31-31-2.
45 (a) There is established the Georgia Community Health Worker Certification Committee.
46 The Commissioner shall appoint the 11 voting members of the committee as follows:
47 (1) One licensed physician with a specialization in primary care or family medicine;
48 (2) One licensed physician or certified nurse midwife with a specialization in maternal
49 and child health;
50 (3) One licensed physician or nurse practitioner with a specialization in geriatrics;
51 (4) One licensed social worker;
52 (5) Two community health worker employers, with special consideration given to care
53 management organizations;
54 (6) Two persons representing training program providers;
55 (7) One person with experience and training in public health policy, with special
56 consideration given to the Georgia Community Health Worker Advocacy Coalition; and
57 (8) Two practicing community health workers, with special consideration given to
58 persons active in the Georgia Community Health Worker Network, provided that such
59 persons are eligible for certification as community health workers in this state and shall
60 obtain such certification within a time frame specified in rules adopted by the committee.
61 (b) The Commissioner shall appoint two agency representatives to serve as nonvoting
62 members of the committee.
63 (c) No member shall serve on the committee for more than two consecutive full terms. A
64 member appointed for less than a full term may serve two consecutive full terms, and a
65 former member shall be eligible again for appointment after a lapse of one or more years.
