66 (d) Members of the committee may be removed from office under the same conditions for
67 removal from office of members of professional licensing boards provided in Code
68 Section 43-1-17.
69 (e) Members shall serve without compensation, but they may be reimbursed by the
70 department, subject to fund availability, in the same manner as state officials and
71 employees for travel and other expenses actually incurred by them in carrying out their
72 duties as members of the committee.
73 31-31-3.
74 (a) The committee shall meet at least quarterly and may meet at such other times at the call
75 of the chairperson or by a majority of the members as necessary to transact its business.
76 Such meetings may be conducted in person, by telephone, by virtual means, or any
77 combination thereof.
78 (b) The committee shall elect a chairperson, vice chairperson, and secretary from among
79 its membership. Such officers shall serve for terms of two years.
80 (c) A majority of the members of the committee shall constitute a quorum and shall have
81 the authority to act upon any matter properly brought before the committee. The
82 committee shall follow all policies and procedures of Chapter 14 of Title 50, relating to
83 open and public meetings.
84 (d) The department shall provide reasonably necessary administrative support for
85 committee activities.
86 (e) The committee shall have the following powers and duties:
87 (1) To set standards and requirements for approval of training programs and to provide
88 a means for programs providing education and training to community health workers
89 prior to January 1, 2026, to become approved training programs;
