90 (2) To set standards and requirements for the certification of community health workers
91 and to provide a means for individuals employed or engaged as community health
92 workers prior to January 1, 2026, to become certified community health workers;
93 (3) To set standards and a means to assess the mastery of core competencies necessary
94 for an individual to become a certified community health worker;
95 (4) To provide for an expedited means for a community health worker duly certified in
96 another jurisdiction to become a certified community health worker in this state;
97 (5) To establish tiered levels of practice as a certified community health worker and the
98 requirements for each established level, including a level that qualifies a certified
99 community health worker to act as an educator or trainer in an approved training
100 program;
101 (6) To establish grounds for complaints related to the practice of certified community
102 health workers and to establish and implement procedures for the review, investigation,
103 and resolution of such complaints;
104 (7) To establish the disciplinary procedures and actions available to the department in
105 connection with complaint resolution; such actions may include a fine, reprimand,
106 probation, censure, suspension, revocation, denial of a certificate issued, or a combination
107 of the foregoing; and
108 (8) To perform such other functions and duties in order to protect public health, safety,
109 and welfare as may be required to carry out this chapter.
110 31-31-4.
111 (a) All training programs in this state shall be approved by the committee with oversight
112 from the department. No entity shall hold itself out as providing training and education for
113 certified community health workers in this state unless its training program has been
114 approved by the committee.
